The '''Centre for Social Investigation''' ('''CSI''') is an [[interdisciplinary]] research group based at [[Nuffield College, Oxford|Nuffield College]], [[University of Oxford|Oxford University]], in [[England]].
The CSI is led by Professor [[Anthony Heath]], CBE, FBA, Emeritus Professor of [[Sociology]] at [[University of Oxford|Oxford University]] and Professor of Sociology at [[University of Manchester|The University of Manchester]]. It was launched officially in March 2015. The Centre aims to address contemporary [[social issues]] of [[public interest]], carrying out authoritative, research on central social issues which draws upon interdisciplinary expertise <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nuffield.ox.ac.uk/study%20here/Pages/Interdisciplinary%20studies.aspx|title=Interdisciplinary studies - Nuffield College, University of Oxford|website=Ox.ac.uk|accessdate=2015-12-20}}</ref> in economics, politics and sociology and related disciplines such as social policy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/?page_id=6|title=About CSI|website=Ox.ac.uk|accessdate=2015-12-20}}</ref> A particular focus is on examining social progress in [[United Kingdom|Britain]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/?page_id=11|title=Social progress in Britain|website=Ox.ac.uk|accessdate=2015-12-20}}</ref> and to this aim, the Centre has undertaken research covering topics including crime,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CSI_4_Crime.pdf |format=PDF |title=CSI 4 : Is crime really falling? |publisher=Csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> education,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CSI_7_Education.pdf |format=PDF |title=CSI 7 : Has our level of education increased? |publisher=Csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> social capital,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CSI_8_Social_Capital.pdf |format=PDF |title=CSI 8 : Social Capital : Are we becoming lonelier and less civic? |publisher=Csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esrc.ac.uk/news-events-and-publications/news/news-items/most-people-in-the-uk-are-less-lonely-apart-from-men-with-low-qualifications/ |title=Most people in the UK are less lonely – apart from men with low qualifications - Economic and Social Research Council |website=Esrc.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-12-20}}</ref> life expectancy,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CSI_1_LifeExpectancy.pdf |format=PDF |title=CSI 1 : Are we living longer? |publisher=Csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> corruption,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/CSI-14-Corruption.pdf |format=PDF |title=CSI 14 : Is Britain becoming more corrupt? |publisher=Csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> food insecurity <ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/CSI-13-Food-insecurity-v3.pdf |format=PDF |title=CSI 13 : Food insecurity and foodbank use |publisher=Csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> and [[William Beveridge|Beveridge]]’s ‘five giants’.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CSI_12_The_Five_Giantsv2.pdf |format=PDF |title=CSI 12 : What progress has been made tackling Beveridge’s five giants? |publisher=Csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.britac.ac.uk/are-we-fighting-the-right-giants/ |title=Are we fighting the right giants? &#124; British Academy Blog |website=Blog.britac.ac.uk |date=2015-03-24 |accessdate=2015-12-20}}</ref> The Centre also undertakes research on inequalities,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/?page_id=173|title=Inequalities|website=Ox.ac.uk|accessdate=2015-12-20}}</ref> including those relating to gender,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CSI_9_Gender_Inequalities.pdf |format=PDF |title=CSI 9 : Is the UK becoming more gender equal? |publisher=Csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> ethnicity <ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CSI_10_Ethnic_Inequalities.pdf |format=PDF |title=CSI 10 : Are we becoming more or less ethnically-divided? |publisher=Csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Jonathan Owen |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/crime-warning-for-alienated-british-muslims-10112083.html |title=Crime warning for ‘alienated’ British Muslims &#124; Crime &#124; News |publisher=The Independent |date=2015-03-16 |accessdate=2015-12-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://leftfootforward.org/2015/03/british-people-with-bangladeshi-and-pakistani-backgrounds-are-three-times-as-likely-to-be-in-poverty/ |title=British people with Bangladeshi and Pakistani backgrounds are three times as likely to be in poverty |publisher=Left Foot Forward |date=2015-03-17 |accessdate=2015-12-20}}</ref> and class.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CSI_11_Class_Inequalities.pdf |format=PDF |title=CSI 11 : Is Class Inequality at KS4 decreasing? |publisher=Csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> The Centre has a strong emphasis on interdisciplinary work and rigorous methods, ranging from [[quantitative research]] to [[field experiment]]s. It has undertaken collaborative work with the UK [[Department for Communities and Local Government]].{{fact|date=December 2015}}
CSI's research is independent and non-partisan; as such, it has no political affiliation or leaning.{{fact|date=December 2015}} The Centre is counselled by an advisory board whose members work in research, policy and the private sector. Unusually for an academic research group, the Centre has a strong emphasis on engaging and disseminating its research beyond traditional academic outputs to communicate the results of its activities in an accessible way to non-technical audiences, including policy-makers and the public more generally. The Centre maintains a blog with posts from both its researchers and from guest contributors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://csi.nuff.ox.ac.uk/|title=CSI Nuffield|website=Ox.ac.uk|accessdate=2015-12-20}}</ref>
