{{italic title}} {{use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} '''''Shtisel''''' ([[Hebrew]]: שטיסל) is an Israeli television drama series that follows the storyline of a fictional ultra-Orthodox [[Haredi]] Jewish family living in the [[Geula]] neighborhood of present-day [[Jerusalem]].<ref name="Ghert-Zand">{{cite news|last1=Ghert-Zand|first1=Renee|title=Why I Can't Stop Watching 'Shtisel'|url=http://forward.com/culture/334808/why-i-cant-stop-watching-shtisel/|accessdate=5 April 2016|work=The Forward|date=4 March 2016}}</ref> Creators and writers are [[Ori Elon]] and [[Yehonatan Indursky]].<ref name="Ghert-Zand" /> The show premiered on [[Yes Oh]] 29 June 2013 and has aired two seasons.
In October 2016, it was announced that [[Amazon.com]] had picked up Shtisel and was planning to remake it set in [[Brooklyn, NY]] under the title ''Emmis''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kamin|first1=Debra|title=Israeli Drama About Ultra-Orthodox Brood Gets American Treatment|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/spotlight/israel-drama-orthodox-brood-gets-american-treatment-1201891017/|accessdate=27 September 2017|work=Variety|date=17 October 2016}}</ref>
