{{for|the language|Xokleng language}}
The '''Xokleng''' or '''Aweikoma''' (sometimes called '''''[[botocudo]]s''''') are a [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]] tribe of [[Brazil]]; their territory is located mainly in the state of [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]]. They were one of the original inhabitants of the province of Misiones in Argentina. They may also sometimes be found on the Ibirama, Posto Velho, and Rio dos Pardos reservations.

